<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772765>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Comparison of typical-looking O. monilis (A), O. elegans sp. nov. (B), O. picta sp. nov. (C), and O. lineata sp. nov. (D). Photos: Conrad Hoskin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772765/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772783>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Holotype of O. lineata sp. nov. (QM J91392; Expedition National Park, Lonesome section, Queensland). Photo: Conrad Hoskin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772783/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772785>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Variation in O. lineata sp. nov.; Arcadia Valley. A–E are adults and F is a juvenile. Photos: Stephen Zozaya (A, B); Conrad Hoskin (C–F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772785/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772787>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Oedura lineata sp. nov. foraging at night in a typical position on the lower trunk of a brigalow tree. Photo: Conrad Hoskin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772787/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772759>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Comparison of O. jowalbinna (A), O. cincta (B), O. castelnaui (C), and O. argentea (D). Photos: Stephen Zozaya (A, B); Conrad Hoskin (C, D)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772759/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3772789>
    dc:description "FIGURE 17. (A) Habitat of O. lineata sp. nov. at Expedition National Park, Lonesome section. (B) View from the national park boundary, showing the cleared grazing land that now dominates the Arcadia Valley. Photos: Conrad Hoskin." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3772789/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

